        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " note), seems to have been widely worshipped in Western Asia. His name occurs frequently on the \"Moabite-Stone.\" Car-Chemish, \"the fort of Chemosh,\" a great city of the northern Hittites, must have been under his protection. In Babylon he seems to have been known as Chomus-belus, or Chemosh-Bel.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The hill - Olivet. At present the most southern summit only (the \"Mons Offensionis\") is pointed out as having been desecrated by the idol sanctuaries: but the early Eastern travelers tell us that in their time the most northern suburb was believed to have been the site of the high p ace of Chemosh, the southern one that of Moloch only. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "The hill - Olivet. At present the most southern summit only (the \"Mons Offensionis\") is pointed out as having been desecrated by the idol sanctuaries: but the early Eastern travelers tell us that in their time the most northern suburb was believed to have been the site of the high p ace of Chemosh, the southern one that of Moloch only. ",
            "children": []
