        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "in the hill that",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " is ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "before Jerusalem",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] The hill facing Jerusalem is the mount of Olives. It is described in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezekiel 11:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " as ‘the mountain which is on the east side of the city,’ and in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Zechariah 14:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " as ‘the mount of Olives, which is before Jerusalem on the east.’ The LXX. (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
